caption: Best poke bowl in town. I used to work pre-downtown pre-covid and would walk there for lunch. Now I will get up off my couch, get out of my pajamas and drive downtown just to go get a bowl.
Fantastic food and the people were very helpful
Delicious food
Great customer service and delicious food!
Best downtown lunch spot.
I go here about 2 times every week! The fresh tuna poke bowls are to die for!! The only place I trust and go to get poke in Louisville!
Great service, great food! Little local hole in the wall with the most quirky and quaint inside!

This place is great. The fish is the freshest tasting fish I've found downtown. Plus the veggies are always crisp and fresh. It's quick, well-priced, and easy to pick up. If you work downtown, you need to stop in here.  Be sure to try the house sauce, the mustard tang goes great with the fish.
Best poke bowl in Downtown Louisville
The best! Owners are great food is great!
Perfect. Owners, food. All on the spot. Really terrific. No sitting room, but its not needed. Pick it up, drive to the park by the river and eat.

Since they opened, I have been going there and they have the best and freshest food in this area. They are fast, clean and most of all whatever you order, it is very good. The owners are very nice and they always try to accommodate your request. I love this place and their price is very reasonable. If you are in the downtown area, make sure to stop by and taste their food, you will not regret it. They are in the corner of 5th and Market St. in downtown Louisville.

This place is my favorite place to eat for lunch break. Healthy stuff, kind and lovely family runs the place and they play calm meditation style music. Been coming here for years and hope they keep it going for a long time. Downtown Louisville needs more local family places and this place is worth a trip.
Great food and good prices. Not a lot of seating room but it's fast service if you want take out.

I really enjoy their bibimbap! It's not stone bowl,but perfect portion for lunch and the bulgogi,banchan vegetables and gochujang are delicious! I can honestly say,as a half Korean, the taste is one of the best in the city.

I moved here from Ohio and there was almost nowhere to find Poke! I was so happy when I found this place, a taste of home. The salad was crisp, the smoked salmon and tuna was very good, they have a lot of dressings, I got seaweed and tofu on my salad, very good. Compared to other Poke places the prices are quite good.

I will not be doing any business with this establishment, since they refuse to pay their bills for services rendered in good faith, not only do they refuse to pay their bills, they lie and dodge all attempts to collect even though the amount owed is not excessive at all, which tells me that the owner of this company does not have a good business ethic.
So good
Great food and fast service
Delicious and fresh
Always incredibly fresh incredibly professional and insanely fast
Awesome, food and fast
So good

I wish they were open more! I don't work downtown and do not get the opportunity to go out for lunch, so when I was in the area for a conference, I made sure to convince my group to go to Pokehana for lunch. Holy cow, so good.

Love this place for lunch. It has a really small storefront and the inside only has a couple of tables. You can’t beat it for carryout. It is only a couple of blocks away and I can get in and out in less than 5 minutes. The food is always piping hot and the staff is friendly. My go-to is fried rice with steak with korean chili and hot sauces. For less than $10 it is really filling!
Always get the hottest sauce they have
Great lunch spot for a quick bowl of poke.
Love the new tacos options. Will be back for them.

The poke is not as fresh as Hawaii but it's still fresh and really good. This place definitely satisfied my poke cravings. The spicy bowl was filled with flavor and had some heat to it. My husband loved the bulgogi he had.
The fish tasted very fresh, the sauces were great and the price is wonderful for the portion and quality. I will go here again very soon.

Best bowl I have had since being stationed in Korea....  If you love to order Asian food this is the place to eat for lunch and dinner.... they have a small sit down but you can order ahead... centrally located so a nice walk from the office.  I brought a long time friend and he was blown away at how good the food was there... hidden treasure!!!!!
I LOVED It here! It’s really well priced, almost cheap considering the generous amount of fresh fish you get and the sweetest workers there. Really hope I come back soon.

I love this place! I eat here at least once a month if not once a week for lunch! They are cheap, super fresh, and delicious. If you like sushi bowls and are thinking about going here I can't recommend it enough. The only downside to this place is that they close at 5 and are not open on the weekends.
Not the most authentic (as in Hawaii), but there is nothing better or closer to it in Louisville.
This place is awesome and fast!
This is nice little place. We love the food. Ginger sauce is awesome
Love Pokehana. Quality is good and consistent, and it is always quick getting in and out. I do wish they offered a low carb alternative to the rice, like riced cauliflower or zucchini noodles.

It's a sad little place to go to. The people there are as dry and cold as the current temperature is right now. The food was bland and the spicy sauce was overpoweringly spicy to the point of not being able to enjoy my food. The tacos were OK but not worth the time and money. It was not a good experience for me. The decoration needs a touch more, because the place is uninviting. Deal with friendly attitude with customers and fix your extremely spicy sauce and maybe I'll be back... add color to the place too! Overall, a big NO for me.
Great value and quality food. You would pay $5 more for a bowl in most cities.
Love this place!!!!
❤️❤️my queen
Fast, friendly, fresh. I will definitely return.
Nice lunch spot. Only 3-starred them because that type of food apparently isn't my thing.
Good food, fair pricing. Great for quick lunch
great quality great prices, if i worked downtown it would be hard not to go everyday!
This place is amazing. My wife and I just got back from Hawaii and she was on this big poke kick. She found out about Pokehana and we love it. Great selection and everything tastes so fresh!
Excellent quick poke bowls.  Perfect for a healthy quick lunch.
More of a takeout place but good poke bowls
Great quality and variety, reasonably priced for sushi grade meats.
The only downfall is they aren't open on saturday and Sunday! Love the food
Honestly, quite mediocre Poke. I've had much better places.
Very tasty, fast casual poke options. Delicious.
AMAZING FOOD! Fish was super fresh (I got the tuna) and everything was very tasty. Service was great as well!
Best poke - so delicious and fresh. Try it!
Perfect lunch option. It's like a burrito bowl but with sushi.
(Translated by Google) Name name name  (Original) Nom nom nom
Fresh and fast. The ingredients seen top notch.
All time fav.  Absolutely delish.  The price for a Poke Bowl is extremely reasonable and the food is really fresh. Super Friendly staff! Highly Recommended!!
Fast, affordable, and fresh.
The sushi bowls are fabulous! And I love the kimchi tacos! Wonderful food for a very reasonable price.
Delicious sushi bowls; unlike anything I've ever had before and bursting with flavors. Their ingredients are very fresh, and you get a lot of food for your money. I will be back!
So good! Everything tastes fresh and it's inexpensive.

This place has definitely turned me onto Poke bowls. I've had a couple of them before in different cities, but never like this. It's like a Chipotle or Qdoba where you can get a bunch of toppings and the amount of fish you get is generous to say the least. I highly recommend you give it a try if you're a fan of sushi!

Had a bowl with fresh and tasty ingredients. The tuna was meaty and the vegetables were crisp. The service preparing the bowl was efficient and Theo menu boards are easy to read and understand. Beyond the bowls, they have some rice dishes on the menu. I have dined in and I would say that the seating is just a few very basic tables. I have not seen it crowded, but I think it would be nice if the seating area was a little more inviting.
I wish there were more vegetables in the fried rice
Great quality food for some quick lunch.

This place is wonderful. The sashimi tasted great and you got a lot of food for your money. Right after my party arrived a group of around ten walked in and they moved the line in 5 minutes. Reasonably priced, great food and quick service. Definitely recommend!

The Hawaiian poké is very yummy. My Hawaiian friends were not as impressed with authenticity, but I still like it. Great tasting bibimbap. They make their own gochujang paste! Clean, simple restaurant.  $8.50 - 9.90 for poké and $8.95 for bibimbap.
